h4 Any player
p
    | #{Constants[Enums.Actions.DISTRACTTHEREF]} is a type of 
    a(href="/actions/#{Enums.Actions.RUN}") #{Constants[Enums.Actions.RUN]} 
    | or
    a(href="/actions/#{Enums.Actions.SPRINT}") #{Constants[Enums.Actions.SPRINT]}
    | . The player attempting to #{Constants[Enums.Actions.DISTRACTTHEREF]}
    | must move adjacent to the Ref using the normal rules. Both players will roll 
    | a 4+ test: One for the player attempting the action, and one for the ref. 

h5 #{Constants[Enums.Actions.DISTRACTTHEREF]} is a 3 dice 4+ test (1)
ul
    li +1 if the player is a #{Constants[Enums.Positions.GUARD]}.

h5 Remain Calm is a 3 dice 4+ test (1)
ul
    li 
        | -1 per player from the distracting player's team threatening the hex the 
        | ref is in (ignoring the distracting player, maximum of -2).

table.table.table-striped
    tr
        td Draw or #{Constants[Enums.Actions.DISTRACTTHEREF]} succeeds.
        td 
            | The Ref focuses entirely on the distracting player. For the rest of 
            | the rush the Ref will only roll dice in a Ref check against the 
            | distracting player. After this rush, the Ref will return to normal. 
            | Roll a 
            a(href="/actions/#{Enums.Actions.REFCHECK}") #{Constants[Enums.Actions.REFCHECK]} 
            | against the distracting player immediately, but do not add a die for 
            | the Eye.
    tr
        td #{Constants[Enums.Actions.DISTRACTTHEREF]} doubles
        td 
            | As above, but the distracting player is so convincing that no ref check 
            | is made against them.
    tr
        td Remain Calm succeeds.
        td 
            | The Ref is unimpressed. Roll a normal #{Constants[Enums.Actions.REFCHECK]}
            | against the distracting player immediately.
    tr
        td Remain Calm doubles.
        td The distracting player is sent off for the rest of the match.
